Package edu.ucsc.cross.hse.core.modeling

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    HybridDynamics<X>
    This interface defines the system state as the parameter X, and outlines the methods that must be implemented to define a hybrid dynamical model of the form documented in the user manual.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    DataStructure
    The base of any data structure developed to use within the environment.
    DataStructureProperties
    The properties of of an object set, which provides information about the set and how it should be handled.
    HybridSystem<X extends DataStructure>
    The base class for implementing hybrid system models.
    HybridSystemComponents<X extends DataStructure>
    The internal components of a hybrid system.
